> <NEW - WHEELIE>
>
> Wheelie did not have an idea of what he was up against, whether friend or
> foe.  At ths point, seeing it stare out, but not approach hi, and vanish
> back to the underbrush, he kept his energon goodies out and about.
>
> SEeing it vanish and not being able to track it further, he put the goodies
> back in his storage unit, then carefully waited again adn listened to see if
> there were more of them, or he was alone again, in which case he would
> carefully move on then.

<NEW>

There is no other detectable sound or movement from out there in the
brush. What ever it was appears to be gone.

Ahead of WHEELIE though the track that he was following appears to
still be there as well as the low hum of energy that seemed to be
present everywhere, at least in this section of this gigantic jungle!

Then dimly, almost hidden in the backround noise a beacon could be
possibly made out. It was not one that relied on the typical comlink
signal, but it seemed to be on a similar frequency as the back ground
hum. It was very dim and faint, as if trying to stay unnoticed. The
only thing that was recognizable about it was that it was an Autobot
beacon!

It was further up the trail, although how much further was difficult to tell!

(TAG)

Preston
